Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, lay the
@skin-on British chicken breasts{2} into the pan, skin-side down. Season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other
side.

Transfer to a #baking tray{}, skin-side up, then roast on the top shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Buttered Potatoes and Cavolo Nero ==

Meanwhile, fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water and @salt{1/2%tsp} and
pop on high heat.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and add to the pan.

Cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{12-15%minutes}. Add the
@chopped cavolo nero{100%g} for the final ~{3-4%minutes} of cooking time.

> TIP: Remove any tough stalks from the cavolo nero.

Once cooked, drain well in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.
Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== Creamy Pesto Sauce ==

While the potatoes cook, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add garlic to the pan. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{100%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Stir and bring to the
boil, then simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2%minutes}.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @fresh pesto{32%g}, then remove from the
heat.

> When the chicken is almost cooked, reheat the sauce if needed. Add a splash of
> water if it's a little thick.

== Finishing ==

Season the cooked cavolo nero and potatoes with @salt{} and pepper. Add the
@butter{15%g} and stir to combine.

Slice the chicken widthways and transfer to your plates.

Share out the cavolo nero and potatoes alongside.

Spoon the creamy pesto sauce over the chicken to finish. Enjoy!